      "name": "Readable",
      "kind": "class",
      "status": "partial",
      "notes": "Readable streams now support push(), read(), pipe(), pause(), resume(), destroy(), destroyed, readable, readableEncoding, and setEncoding('utf8'/'utf-8'). The current setEncoding() slice is UTF-8-only and covers buffered and flowing string decoding for Buffer/byte[] backed chunks. pipe() keeps the minimal backpressure integration: when destination.write(...) returns false, forwarding pauses until the destination emits drain.",
