  "notes": "The stream baseline now includes lifecycle controls and helpers that are useful to higher-level Node modules: pause()/resume(), UTF-8 setEncoding(), destroy()/destroyed, callback-style pipeline(...), callback-style finished(...), and deterministic writable drain/finish/error teardown. Important gaps remain: objectMode, cork()/uncork(), richer write() callback semantics, AbortSignal support, node:stream/promises, binary/socket-oriented encoding breadth, and the more complex teardown/buffering edge cases that full Node parity requires."
